Crying. My brave boy. I can’t believe how far we have come in the past few years. 

In honor of National bleeding 🩸 disorder awareness month I wanted to share more of Greyson’s story ❤️ Greyson was diagnosed with severe hemophilia B - (a genetic bleeding disorder that causes his blood to not clot) when he was only 4 months old. 

Every week he gets an IV placed (usually in his hand or arm) to infuse him with factor 9 since his body doesn’t produce any! Little bumps and bruises that normally wouldn’t matter could mean a trip to the emergency room for him. 

I’m so proud of my sweet boy and everything he has overcome and I love my little bestie beyond words. 

#severehemophilia #hemophilia #hemophiliac #reels #raredisease #rare #severehemophiliab #bleedingdisorders #hemomom #bleedingdisorderawarenessmonth #hemophiliaawareness

There is no timeline with grief. We can’t control how long it takes or how many times it starts over. For me, it’s taken a year. The longest year of my life. And there are days I worry it’s starting all over again. I wouldn’t wish postpartum anxiety on my worst enemy 😢

Love you forever my baby boy 💙

My baby girl is SEVEN! 💗

Peyton is beautiful, kind, silly and has been my very best friend since the day she was born! She’s always worried about others and is the best big sister and friend to everyone. She still loves everything princess, dolls and makeup. I’m so beyond grateful to be her mom and love watching her grow. 

Happy 7th birthday sweet girl! 🎉😚

SWIPE ➡️ to see her at every age 🥺
Sharing a birthday with my best friend is one of the greatest things I have ever been blessed with 💜🥺 I still can’t believe my girl is 7!!

My heart breaks with every birthday. I hate to see time moving so fast and wish more than anything I could freeze it and keep my babies small forever but also nothing brings me more joy than to watch them grow older. Motherhood is a wild ride with so many emotions but I’m so glad I’m here to experience it 🤍
